content.title: Is OpenAI's Microsoft partnership a threat to Apple?
content.description:
Apple's (AAPL) market cap has crossed past $4 trillion on Tuesday. This comes after Microsoft (MSFT) and OpenAI (OPAI.PVT) agreed to a new for-profit deal, with Microsoft's stake now valued at $135 billion.

Prairie Operating Co. EVP Market Strategy Lou Basenese discusses what this news could mean for Apple. The iPhone maker is due to report fiscal fourth quarter earnings results after the market close this Thursday, October 30.

Basenese is also the founder of TheBigSkinny.com.

Also catch Lou Basenese weigh in on Amazon's (AMZN) latest round of layoffs and what it may be signaling about the broader US economy.

To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

content.title: Apple seeks to end Apple Pay trade secrets lawsuit
content.summary: (Reuters) -Apple urged a federal judge to dismiss a racketeering lawsuit by a company that accused the iPhone maker of stealing its technology to create the lucrative mobile wallet Apple Pay.  In a Monday night filing in Atlanta federal court, Apple said if the case is not dismissed, it should be transferred to a Texas judge who recently dismissed Fintiv's related patent case.  Fintiv, based in Austin, Texas, accused Apple of misappropriating technology for Apple Pay that it had once sought to license from CorFire, a Georgia company that Fintiv bought in 2014.
